This file contains more detailed doctests for the stdnum.cn.ric. It
tries to cover more corner cases and detailed functionality that is not
really useful as module documentation.

>>> from stdnum.cn.ric import *  # noqa
>>> from stdnum.exceptions import *  # noqa


Normal values that should just work.

>>> validate('360426199101010071')
'360426199101010071'
>>> validate('44011320141005001x')
'44011320141005001X'


Get the birth date:

>>> get_birth_date('360426199101010071')
datetime.date(1991, 1, 1)
>>> get_birth_date('44011320141005001x')
datetime.date(2014, 10, 5)


Get the birth place:

>>> get_birth_place('360426199101010071')['county']
u'\u5fb7\u5b89\u53bf'
>>> get_birth_place('44011320141005001x')['county']
u'\u756a\u79ba\u533a'


Invalid format:

>>> validate('36042619910101007V')
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidFormat: ...
>>> validate('T60426199101010078')
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidFormat: ...


Invalid date:

>>> validate('360426199113010079')
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidComponent: ...


Invalid checksum:

>>> validate('36042619910102009X')
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidChecksum: ...


Invalid location:

>>> validate('990426199112010074')  # unknown birth place code
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidComponent: ...
